TYPICAL EXPRESSION

3x^3 + 2x^2 + x + 1



RULE FOR POWER

look for ^
look at left side
store digit(s) i.e. coefficient = digit(s) before 'x'
look at right side
store exponent i.e exponent = digit(s) after '^' and before '+'
replace power with
coefficent*exponent - 1
append x ^ exponent - 1


RULE FOR LINEAR
replace x with 1



RULE FOR CONSTANT
if isDigit() = true
  replace with 0
